snippet.title: Indoor Playground Area for Kids in Coppell, TX - MUST VISIT!
snippet.description:
http://www.urbanairtrampolinepark.com/coppell-indoor-playground/ – Best playhouse to entertain children indoor. Visit this specially developed area for kids from Coppell (TX), or from one of the surrounding cities (Carrollton, Flower Mound or Lewisville Texas).

Organizing a kids birthday party and looking for a birthday party place? You have now found it! Our safe Indoor Kids Playhouse now houses the TUBES Playground. The TUBES Attraction Is Included With All Birthday party Packages

Urban Air Coppell brings the indoor playground experience to a whole new level with our TUBES Attraction. The TUBES Indoor Playground is an interactive adventure zone designed to allow imaginations to run wild.

The Indoor Playground elements provide fun experiences for your kiddo, and also enhance fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination and sensory development.

Urban Air Indoor Trampoline Park Coppell is open 7 days a week and hosts a variety of activities for kids, tweens, teens and adults. Urban Air is the perfect way to have fun and stay fit.

Our Coppell TUBES attraction and the Trampoline Park, located just off the Sam Rayburn (121) Tollway next to Sprouts, is the perfect destination for Coppell, Lewisville, Carrollton, Farmers Branch and Las Colinas Trampoline Park enjoyment, and will provide weekly events and kids birthday parties for all ages and fitness levels.

snippet.description:
This video shares 16 at home activities you can do with your toddler. I’ve been working on this video for too long. But, with many people stuck at home, I hustled to finally get it done! I originally started this post with 1-year-olds in mind. That’s how old my little guy is. But, many of these will work for 2 and even 3-year-olds as well.

#momvlog #toddler

See 13 more learning activities for toddlers: https://youtu.be/qXW7oNtA0Pc

Read the post for more info: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/16-activities-to-do-at-home-with-your-young-toddler/

Get the Lovevery Play Kit Subscriptions: https://www.butfirstcoffeeblog.com/recommends/lovevery-play-kits/

Tips for Playing with 1-Year-Olds
Model the Activity: Very often you’ll need to model an activity for a toddler. We can’t always just put it in front of them an expect they know what to do. Show your child the way to play with it and then offer it back.
Parallel Play – Parallel play can often help extend the length of time your little one plays. Parallel play is when you see two kids playing next to each other but not actually with each other. You can mimic that same thing by “playing” to encourage them to continue playing with whatever toy they have.
At their level tables and shelves – It’s super helpful to make your space accessible for your little one. Having toy shelves that are right at their level is ideal. It’s also great if you have a toddler-height table for them to use. It’s a little more expensive, but I also really love using a learning tower, which allows kids to stand at counter-height in the kitchen to play and do activities.

Best  Day Ever 1003

Nobody's home!! Jenny went to breakfast with her sister and took Niko Bear with here, so Adley and I are home alone and can do whatever we want and be a load as we want!! Now that we don't need to follow our normal routine, we head upstairs to jump on the bed!! That's fun, but we want to have more fun. So we think of what we can do. Adley has the great idea of going to Rush! It's one of her favorite places because they have games and bounce houses and inflatable horses!

But guess what, they also have something that Aldey has never done before, roller skating! We decide that now that she's a 4 year old that she can try it for the first time! We get some skates. We get he cutest little skates and put them on Adley. We then have to walk to the indoor skate park and its a struggle muffin! Adley is all over the place, slipping around and doing the splits. I help her over to the rink where we skate around for a while! It's so fun watching her learn new things!!

After we've had fun roller skating, we head over to the bounce houses where Adley does all sorts of tricks. I'm in there too, till they kick me out for not being a kid lol! We then head over to the drift carts so Adley can go for a ride and, another first, we try out the ginormous bumper cars. Adley loves them!! We then end our daddy daughter family fun date with Ice cream!

Before this best day is over, I need pack.
